<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="307" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1127,219,1044]" pageId="8" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,404,603,627]" pageId="8" pageNumber="307">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species belongs to the 
<emphasis box="[770,857,605,628]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="307">nigripes</emphasis>
group and resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Hendel, 1922" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Agromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phragmitidis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="307">A. phragmitidis</emphasis>
Hendel, 1922
</taxonomicName>
, which differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Černý, 2011" authorityName="Černý" authorityYear="2011" box="[658,821,637,660]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Agromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elladanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[658,821,637,660]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="307">A. elladanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[828,911,636,659]" pageId="8" pageNumber="307" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as follows: the eyes are very large, slightly pubescent; the parafacials are not visible in front of the eye in profile; 3 ori setae of the same length are well developed; the gena is highest in the posterior part reaching 0.10–0.17 height of the eye; the wing apex is placed at tip of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[942,966,747,762]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="307">4+5</subScript>
. The male terminalia of both species are clearly different (see 
<bibRefCitation author="GRIFFITHS G. C. D." box="[674,838,763,788]" pageId="8" pageNumber="307" pagination="113 - 168" refId="ref30067" refString="GRIFFITHS G. C. D. 1963: A revision of the Palaearctic species of the nigripes group of the genus Agromyza Fallen. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie 106: 113 - 168." type="journal article" year="1963">GRIFFITHS 1963</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="SPENCER K. A." box="[849,1000,763,788]" pageId="8" pageNumber="307" pagination="305 - 606" refId="ref30763" refString="SPENCER K. A. 1976: The Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica. Vol. 5. Scandinavian Science Press Ltd., Klampenborg, Part 1 (pp. 1 - 304), Part 2 (pp. 305 - 606)." type="book chapter" year="1976">SPENCER 1976</bibRefCitation>
). Structures of the male terminalia are very similar to the Afrotropical species 
<taxonomicName authority="Spencer, 1985" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Agromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graminaceae">
<emphasis box="[859,1028,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="307">A. graminaceae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="SPENCER K. A." pageId="8" pageNumber="307" pagination="969 - 1027" refId="ref30816" refString="SPENCER K. A. 1985: East African Agromyzidae (Diptera): further descriptions, revisionary notes and new records. Journal of Natural History 19: 969 - 1027." type="journal article" year="1985">Spencer, 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[508,578,828,852]" name="Kenya" pageId="8" pageNumber="307">Kenya</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="SPENCER K. A." box="[593,744,827,852]" pageId="8" pageNumber="307" pagination="969 - 1027" refId="ref30816" refString="SPENCER K. A. 1985: East African Agromyzidae (Diptera): further descriptions, revisionary notes and new records. Journal of Natural History 19: 969 - 1027." type="journal article" year="1985">SPENCER 1985</bibRefCitation>
). However, this species is characterized by a broad epistoma, a short ocellar triangle and yellowish-grey calypters with a dark, brownish fringe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="307" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1127,219,1044]" pageId="8" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,924,948]" pageId="8" pageNumber="307">Etymology.</emphasis>
